{"id":"7344","name":"Specific YouTube Time Sharing","tagline":"This Shortcut helps you to share YouTube videos at a specific time you want.","icon":"ios14 c4282601983 g59699","latest":"22667","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><br></p>\n<h4>What does it do:</h4>\n\n<p>If you ever needed a quick way to share YouTube videos at a specific time in the video, this shortcut is your best choice, as it helps you share any YouTube URL, either by copying the link and running the shortcut itself or just using the iPhone sharing API</p>\n<p><br>\n</p><h4>How to use it:</h4>\n<h6>You can use it by:</h6><p></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Copying the YouTube URL from anywhere and running the shortcut by itself, in the shortcuts app</li>\n<li>Sharing from the browser*</li>\n<li>Sharing directly from the YouTube IOS app*</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>*Note1:</strong> The \"<em>Sharing from the browser</em>\" option requires that you use IOS sharing, as it is the only way that shortcuts will appear for execution.</p>\n<p><strong>*Note2:</strong> The \"<em>Sharing directly from the YouTube IOS app</em>\" requires that you use the \"more\" option after pressing the YouTube sharing button to go to the IOS sharing sheet. This has the same motive as \"Note1\"</p>\n<p><strong>Note3:</strong> This shortcut supports time measured in minutes and seconds, if you choose a video longer than 60 minutes, <strong>you have to put the hours in minutes</strong></p>\n<p><br>\n</p><h4>It supports these listed languages:</h4><p></p>\n<ul>\n<li>English (US)</li>\n<li><del>Portuguese (BR)*</del></li>\n</ul>\n<p><del><strong>*Note1:</strong> The Portuguese version has to be downloaded separately <a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/7349/\" title=\"Portuguese Version\"><strong>Here</strong></a> </del>. <strong>Currently Unavailable</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note2:</strong> Language is not essential for this shortcut to work properly, it is just a plus in personalization.</p>\n<p><br>\n</p><h4>Development and Feedback info:</h4>\nTh